===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|plege}}, from {{der|en|xno|plege}}, from {{der|en|fro|plege}} (Modern {{cog|fr|pleige}}) from {{der|en|ML.|plevium}}, {{m|la|plebium}}, from {{m|la|plebiō||I pledge}}, from {{der|en|frk|*plehan||to pledge; to support; to guarantee}}. Akin to {{cog|goh|pflegan||to take care of, be accustomed to}}, {{cog|osx|plegan||to vouch for}}, {{cog|ang|plēon||to risk, endanger}}. More at {{l|en|plight}}.

